{"id":23,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":23,"title":"Chapter 20: Alma and Nehor","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 20"],["h1","Alma and Nehor"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_023_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p3"},"Before King Mosiah died, the Nephites chose judges to lead them. Alma the Younger became the first chief judge. He was also the leader of the Church."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/29.41-42"},"Mosiah 29:41–42"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_023_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p5"},"A large, strong man named Nehor began teaching lies. He said everyone would be saved whether they were good or bad. Many people believed Nehor."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/1.2-5"},"Alma 1:2–5"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_023_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p7"},"Nehor preached against God’s Church, but a righteous man named Gideon defended it. Nehor argued with Gideon, but Gideon spoke with the words of God."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/1.7-8"},"Alma 1:7–8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_023_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p9"},"Nehor became angry and drew his sword and killed Gideon."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/1.9"},"Alma 1:9"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_023_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p11"},"Nehor was taken to Alma to be judged. Nehor boldly defended himself."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/1.10-11"},"Alma 1:10–11"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_023_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p13"},"But Alma said Nehor was guilty because he had taught the people to be wicked and had killed Gideon."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/1.12-13"},"Alma 1:12–13"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_023_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p15"},"Alma said Nehor had to be punished for killing Gideon. According to the law, Nehor must die."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/1.14"},"Alma 1:14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_023_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p17"},"Nehor was taken to a nearby hill and put to death. Before he died he said everything he had taught was wrong. But many people still believed Nehor’s evil teachings."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/1.15-16"},"Alma 1:15–16"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_023_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p19"},"These people loved riches and would not obey God’s commandments. They made fun of the Church members and argued and fought with them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/1.16,19-20,22"},"Alma 1:16, 19–20, 22"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_023_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p21"},"The righteous people continued to obey the commandments and did not complain even when Nehor’s followers hurt them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/1.25"},"Alma 1:25"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_023_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p23"},"The Church members shared everything they had with the poor, and they cared for the sick. They obeyed the commandments, and God blessed them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-20-alma-and-nehor.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/1.27,31"},"Alma 1:27, 31"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
